text.tspan: A portion of our agribusiness farmland is being transitioned to an
auto-regenerative food forest. We expect this change to eventually
increase the net profit per acre while it restores habitat and becomes
The project is sustainably self-funded through its returns on
investments in regenerative food-forest related technologies.
Sometime over the next hundred years, there is likely to come a time
when A.I., humanoid robots, and smart contracts start to build upon
each other and then develop rapidly. Such development could allow
regenerative food systems to shift from the intense manual labour they
require today to a level of automation on par with that of agribusiness.
Such automation would allow regenerative food forests to scale in a
meaningful way and allow more people to adopt the practice. Such
food forests are likely to be situated between towns or cities and their
surrounding agribusiness farmlands. They may be privately owned, co-
ops, or even public utilities set up as extensions of municipal
watersheds or integrated with a region's composting facilities.
Public link to this one page overview of the Hundred-yeare Farm Project: https://github.com/hundredyearfarms/
